        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 1:15PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Bearden, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Beggs...                          Preston...
Okmulgee...                       Okemah...
Okfuskee...                       Clearview...
Mason...                          Okmulgee State Park...
Castle...                         Bearden...
Welty...                          Pharoah...
Slick...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 212 and
232.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
